<activity xml:id="act-dibujosEnBaseDiez" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p>Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>Alike: They both represent <m>262 - 135</m>. They both used a ten to get more ones so they could subtract 5 ones. Both ended up with 12 ones.</li>
<li>Different: Jada broke a ten into ten ones. Han did too, but he kept them together like a ten.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
      <li><ol>
<li>
<m>262-135</m>, which is 127.</li>
<li>
<m>252-132</m>, which is 120.</li>
<li>
<m>252-181</m>, which is 71.</li>
</ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


